<br>
I'm sure there are plenty of these messages floating around this board, but what the hey, I'll add mine.<br>
<br>
I've decided to grace these fair lands with my presence.  Now, while not exactly fresh from the turnip cart, I might as well be.  I used to roam the realm of Bristlebane, as a wood elf *shudder* druid *shudder more, duck insults*, named Eyston (just in case Elani somehow reads this.. miss you).  I sorta retired as the lands of Kunark were about to be discovered.  Anywho ... I'm back.  I tried to get back into things with Eyston, but I feel like an idiot.  Too many changes.  Nothing like being a 50 year old tenderfoot.  After making a fool of myself by trying my best to not make a fool of myself, I've decided to start over.  It's the only decent thing to do.<br>
<br>
And here we are.<br>
<br>
Well.  This time, no squirrel elf for me.  Decided to show myself some respect, so I'm back to my roots, playing a dark elf rogue ... a damn handsome one to be exact.  Despite what you're thinking, never been one to have too much pride.  All those warriors clad in plate can have the glory.  Doesn't matter much to me.  I'd rather greet a challenge from behind, with a dagger to the back.  All the danger seems to be in front of the beasty, not sure why you'd wanna charge right into it.  Just seems silly to me, although I'm glad there's plenty of fame seekers making my job easier.<br>
<br>
So far, I've managed to survive 8 years in the lands.  I'm amazed at the little things.  The frustration of starting over is so great, that it makes any minor accomplishment heaven.  After surviving for 6 years on my first dagger, I ventured to the commonlands to find a snake fang.  And by golly, I did.  Some tree, yes, a tree, was killing darkweeds like it was his job.  I poked the tree.  I told him I wanted a fang, and I could pay.  The dang thing spoke jibberish at me.  But I was persistent.  After shouting fang at it for a good minute, I got one.  Only cost me 2pp (or in my terms at the time, a few hundred fire beetle eyes ... ugh).  That was the happiest day of my life.  I love my fang.<br>
<br>
Oh yeah, my name is Viren.  No particular reason, except that I like it.<br>
<br>
So far, Firiona Vie is a mixed bag.  Its strengths are its weaknesses.  It just feels so big right now.  There is no one.  It is so quiet, and feels so empty.  Nektulos forest is complete and utter pain.  Nothing.  Empty.  I don't know what to do next.  If I have to kill another skeleton, I'm going to go insane.  I wasn't made for soloing!!!  Where are y'all hiding?  I feel left out, I wanna have fun too =)<br>
<br>
It's hard to roleplay with only the guards.  Although I must say the surveyor *whistle* she's a looker.<br>
<br>
<br>
Anyways, I sure hope to grace some of you with my presence in the near future.<br>
<br>
-Viren-<br>
8th year rogue... no fancy title (yet)<br>
